{
  "texts": [
    "Activation visualisation is a straightforward technique to understand the model's behaviour.",
    "The first convolutional layer usually learns simple features like colour and edges, while the last one learns more complex features.",
    "The LIME technique approximates the classification behaviour of a DL model using a simpler, more interpretable model, such as a linear model or a regression tree.",
    "The simple model defines the significance of the features of the input image as a proxy for the significance of the features to the DL model.",
    "This section is devoted to the experimental evaluation of the proposed TL approach in detecting abnormalities in the shoulder."
  ]
}